// Consumer — half of the multi-program axon-passing demo.
//
// Receives the axon vector the producer made (handed off by `_run.py`
// via a serialized wire format) and exposes three `axon_item` reads:
// `animal_2`, `color_1`, `user_1`. The other two keys producer added
// (`animal_1`, `color_2`) are never referenced — that's exactly the
// slice the spec's lazy-materialization optimization (axons.md §"Lazy
// evaluation across boundaries") would be allowed to drop from the
// wire to push the practical capacity higher.
//
// The consumer deliberately returns the raw recovered vector rather
// than running `argmax_cosine` against a decoy pool. That keeps the
// demo focused on the wire-passing mechanism: the orchestrator does
// host-side cosine analysis as monitoring (per CLAUDE.md "numpy is
// allowed for monitoring") to verify that the recovered vector is
// closer to the producer-bundled filler than to vectors that were
// never bundled. Capacity / argmax-reliability is a separate axis
// (see planning/findings/2026-04-22-rotation-binding-capacity-results.md).

function vector recover_animal(vector state) {
    return axon_item(state, "animal_2");
}

function vector recover_color(vector state) {
    return axon_item(state, "color_1");
}

function vector recover_user(vector state) {
    return axon_item(state, "user_1");
}

function string main() {
    return "consumer-loaded";
}
